According to this [site|https://www.kernel.org/pub/software/scm/git/docs/git-log.html]:
{quote}
By default, the commits are shown in reverse chronological order.

--date-order
Show no parents before all of its children are shown, but otherwise show commits in the commit timestamp order.
{quote}
and this [site|http://git-scm.com/book/en/Git-Basics-Viewing-the-Commit-History]:
{quote}
By default, with no arguments, git log lists the commits made in that repository in reverse chronological order. That is, the most recent commits show up first. 
{quote}

It seems that the graph view date order option that the output from the command 'git log' with the default reverse chronological order not with the option '--date-order'.

h2. Improvement suggestion
I think it'd be incredibly useful to have {{⌘F}} and/or {{⇧⌘F}} keyboard shortcuts for setting the insertion point/cursor within the various filter/find search fields, e.g.: 
{code:none}
- (IBAction)performFindPanelAction:(id)sender {
    [self.window makeFirstResponder:searchTextField];
}
{code}
h2. Potential implementation
h3. Bookmarks View
{{⌘F}} could position cursor in search field to quickly filter bookmarks within *Bookmarks View*
h3. File Status View
{{⌘F}} could position cursor in search field to quickly filter files within *File Status View*
h3. Log View
{{⌘F}} could perhaps switch the view over to the *Search View* since there is no search field in *Log View* (also, being able to use {{⌘J}} as a shortcut to _"Jump to"_ commit hash/branch within the *Log View* would be handy)
h3. Search View
{{⌘F}} could position cursor in search field. It might be good to assign {{⇧⌘F}} to be able to accomplish the same behavior when done from any of the 3 main views as well (emulating Xcode's shortcut for _"Find in Workspace"_)

There are some strings untranslated into Japanese:
"Hg Flow" = "Hg フロー";
"Git Flow" = "Git フロー";
"Git Flow / Hg Flow" = "Git フロー / Hg フロー";
"Abort [Action]" = "[アクション] を中止";
"Standard included git-flow" = "標準の内蔵 git-flow";
"Embedded git-flow" = "内蔵 git-flow";
"System git-flow" = "システムの git-flow";
And there are some mistranslated strings:
"I agree to the SourceTree license agreement" = "SourceTree 使用許諾契約を承認します";
"Continue [Action]" = "[アクション] を続ける";
"Use Graft instead of Transplant if available" = "使用可能であれば、Transplant のかわりに Graft を使用する";
"Default usernames for URL which do not include one" = "以下を含む URL ではデフォルトのユーザー名を使用しない";
"Display multiple branch heads in sidebar" = "複数のブランチヘッドをサイドバーに表示する";
"Pull count for current branch only" = "現在のブランチのプルだけをカウントする";
"Use the staging area" = "ステージング領域を使用する";
"Stage files on double click" = "ダブルクリックでファイルをステージする";
"Check submodules before commit & push" = "サブモジュールをチェックしてからコミット & プッシュする";
"Open links on github.com with SourceTree" = "github.com のリンクを SourceTree で開く";
"Disable SSL validation (note: potentially insecure)" = "SSL 証明書を検証しない (注意: 危険性があります)";
"Do not fast-forward when merging, always create commit" = "マージの際に高速前進マージを使用せず、常にコミットを作成する";
"Display author date instead of commit date in log" = "コミット日時ではなく作成日時を履歴に表示";
If you have a margin for time, please let me know to release a newer version in advance and give me a few days to translate it into Japanese.
And if SourceTree for Windows has translatable resources, I can also do it for Windows version.
I'm happy to localize SourceTree.
